💳 Credit Card Fraud Detection using Neural Networks & CNN
👨‍💻 Team Members
Krish Agarwal (2301730146)
U. Nijaagna (2301730196)
📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on detecting fraudulent credit card transactions using Deep Learning techniques, specifically Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN).
The system analyzes transaction patterns and identifies whether a transaction is fraudulent or legitimate, helping reduce financial risks in digital payment systems.

🚨 Problem Statement
Credit card fraud is increasing rapidly with the growth of digital transactions. Fraudulent transactions are rare, making the dataset highly imbalanced, which makes detection challenging.
This project aims to build an automated system that can accurately detect fraud using advanced deep learning models.

🎯 Objectives
Understand and analyze transaction data
Perform data preprocessing and feature scaling
Handle class imbalance using SMOTE
Build and train ANN and CNN models
Compare model performance
Detect fraudulent transactions with high accuracy
📊 Dataset
Source: Kaggle Credit Card Fraud Dataset
Contains anonymized transaction data
Highly imbalanced dataset (very few fraud cases)
⚙️ Tech Stack
Language: Python
Libraries: Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn
Deep Learning: TensorFlow, Keras
Preprocessing: StandardScaler, SMOTE
🧠 Models Used
🔹 Artificial Neural Network (ANN)
Fully connected layers
Learns patterns from transaction data
🔹 Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)
Uses Conv1D layers
Captures complex patterns more effectively
📈 Results
Both models achieved high accuracy (~99%)
CNN performed slightly better in terms of loss
Models successfully detected fraud despite class imbalance
📊 Key Insights
Handling imbalance (SMOTE) is crucial
Feature scaling improves performance
CNN can capture deeper patterns than ANN
Recall is important to reduce missed fraud cases
🚀 Future Scope
Deploy using Flask / FastAPI
Real-time fraud detection system
Use advanced models like Autoencoders
Integrate with banking systems
📎 How to Run
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run the project
python main.py
⭐ Conclusion
This project demonstrates that Deep Learning (ANN + CNN) can effectively detect fraudulent transactions and improve financial security systems.
